At City Beach, our people are at the core of what we do, both our customers
and our team. All are welcome under the City Beach roof, where value is placed
on individual style, teamwork, authenticity, adaptability, and a desire to
exceed expectations.  
  
We stock some of the world's biggest brands across surf, skate, streetwear,
and fashion. Our stores are a hub that connect our customers to events,
influencers, and trends, allowing them to live life on their terms.  
  
** The role **   
The purpose of the ** Women's Product Designer & Developer ** role is to take
ownership of the seasonal products from design phase through to receiving into
the warehouse.  
  
You will work closely with suppliers, buyers, and other stakeholders
throughout the production process and have a significant impact on the
development and maintenance of high-quality product, ultimately managing
production costs and driving company profit.  

** What do you need to do? **

  * Liaise with overseas and local suppliers, managing the critical path of inhouse product to ensure timelines, quality and margin are adhered to and suppliers have necessary technical packs. 
  * Assist in following up suppliers in relation to sampling timelines and invoicing, providing weekly updates. 
  * Source new suppliers and negotiate supplier agreements under the guidance of the Women’s Production and Development Coordinator. 
  * Oversee import logistics and costs, accounting for quality and accuracy of incoming samples and stock. 
  * Research and identify trends, enabling relevant and concise sourcing. 
  * Understand Supply Chain process, Intellectual property, copyright and trademarking requirements. 
  * Manage end to end production cycle of inhouse brands, including cost negotiation, terms of trade, delivery, product and supplier requirements and stakeholder engagement. 
  * Ability to prioritise and execute high volume workload with attention to detail and within given timelines. 
  * Demonstrate strong written and verbal communication skills, with high attention to detail. 
  * Exhibit a deep understanding of construction, knowledge of fabrications and trims for categories.   

** What are we looking for? **

  * Must have ** youth ** fashion design and product development experience, similar brands are preferable. 
  * The ability to identify trends relevant to City Beach customers. 
  * Tertiary qualification in fashion, design or related fields highly desired. 
  * Previous experience in managing fashion production team, offshore experience is essential. 
  * Proficient in the Microsoft Suite and mid–high level competency with Illustrator and Photoshop CAD. 

  
** The benefits: **

  * Competitive and negotiable salary package for the right candidate. 
  * We have partnered with industry leaders to bring our team members discounts on products and memberships to keep you healthy on all fronts: 
    * Access to a free Employee Assistance Program 
    * 7% Medibank Private discount 
    * Goodlife Health Clubs & Fitness First Gyms membership discounts 
    * Retail partner discounts through Rest Super on food, beauty, health, fashion, furniture and technology products 
  * Enjoy a 35% team member discount for you, your friends and family to access. 
  * Endless progression and career opportunities across all departments in Head Office, Retail Stores and our Distribution Centre. 
  * Birthday and work anniversary celebrations and shared lunches. 
  * Social work drinks every Friday night at 4pm! 

If you have experience as a Product Developer / Designer for a youth fashion
brand, we want to speak with you!

